    "title_en": "Physics and Astrophysics of Black Holes with eXTP",
    "abstract_en": "The enhanced X-ray Timing and Polarimetry (eXTP) mission will combine spectral, timing, and polarimetric techniques to study accreting black holes, measure their masses and spins, and test Einstein's theory of General Relativity in the strong-field regime. In this contribution, I review the capabilities of eXTP to advance our current understanding of black hole physics and astrophysics.",
